n, Lanarkshire, Skotland, United Kingdom","Lamington, Lanarkshire, Scotland, United Kimgdom":"Lamington, Lanarkshire, Skotland, United Kingdom","Scotland, United Kimgdom":"Skotland","Lamington, Ayrshire, Scotland,":"Ayrshire, Skotland","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Skotland","Drowned - Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Skotland","Seton, East Lothian, Scotland, United Kimgdom":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Skotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Skotland, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1323–1381":"1323–1381","1320–1389":"1320–1389","1338–1374":"1338–1374","1345–1432":"1345–1432","1305–1333":"1305–1333","1310–Female":"1310–Overleden","1374":"1374","1381":"1381","1338":"1338","1305":"1305","19 July 1333":"19 juli 1333","1323":"1323","1345":"1345","1389":"1389","1333":"1333","1432":"1432","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","1329":"1329","Lamington, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lamington, Lanarkshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Lamington, Lanarkshire, Scotland, United Kimgdom":"Lamington, Lanarkshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Scotland, United Kimgdom":"Schotland","Lamington, Ayrshire, Scotland,":"Ayrshire, Schotland","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Schotland","Drowned - Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Schotland","Seton, East Lothian, Scotland, United Kimgdom":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Scotland":"Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1323–1381":"1323–1381","1320–1389":"1320–1389","1338–1374":"1338–1374","1345–1432":"1345–1432","1305–1333":"1305–1333","1310–Female":"1310–Deceased","1374":"1374","1381":"1381","1338":"1338","1305":"1305","19 July 1333":"19 July 1333","1323":"1323","1345":"1345","1389":"1389","1333":"1333","1432":"1432","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","1329":"1329","Lamington, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lamington, Lanarkshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Lamington, Lanarkshire, Scotland, United Kimgdom":"Lamington, Lanarkshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland, United Kimgdom":"Scotland","Lamington, Ayrshire, Scotland,":"Ayrshire, Scotland","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Drowned - Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Scotland","Seton, East Lothian, Scotland, United Kimgdom":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Seton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish (Midlothian) and English: variant of   Seaton  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Seaton","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places called Seaton, such as those in Cumberland, Devon, Durham, Leicestershire, Northumberland, Rutland, East Yorkshire, and North Yorkshire, most of which derive from Old English <i>sǣ</i> ‘sea, lake’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’, though the Leicestershire placename probably arises from an Old English personal name <i>Sǣga</i> or a stream-name <i>Sǣge</i> (from Old English <i>sǣge</i> ‘slow moving’; compare   Seabrook  ) + Old English <i>tūn</i>.","Scottish: habitational name from Seton (East Lothian), from Old English <i>sǣ</i> ‘sea’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."]}]},{"name":"Isabella","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."],"variants":[{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]}]},{"name":"Marion","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a medieval French diminutive form of   Marie  , introduced to Britain in the Middle Ages. In some places it was taken as a pet form of   Margaret   or   Margery .  As a male name, it is an altered form of the Continental male name <i>Marian</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>Marianus</i> (from   Marius  ), but is now rarely, if ever, used. It was the birth name of the American film star  John Wayne  (  1907–79 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Isabella Marion Seton was born in 1323, in Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, her father, Sir William Seton,, was 18 and her mother, Lady Catherine Sinclair, was 13. She married William Baliol of Hoprig, 2nd of Lamington in Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1381, in Lamington, Lanarkshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1323–1381":"1323–1381","1320–1389":"1320–1389","1338–1374":"1338–1374","1345–1432":"1345–1432","1305–1333":"1305–1333","1310–Female":"1310–Surnud","1374":"1374","1381":"1381","1338":"1338","1305":"1305","19 July 1333":"19. juuli 1333","1323":"1323","1345":"1345","1389":"1389","1333":"1333","1432":"1432","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","1329":"1329","Lamington, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lamington, Lanarkshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Lamington, Lanarkshire, Scotland, United Kimgdom":"Lamington, Lanarkshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland, United Kimgdom":"Scotland","Lamington, Ayrshire, Scotland,":"Ayrshire, Scotland","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Drowned - Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Scotland","Seton, East Lothian, Scotland, United Kimgdom":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1323–1381":"1323–1381","1320–1389":"1320–1389","13